 Here, we see that $12012_3$ is a base three number and we are asked to convert it to base ten. We know that each digit in i a base three number represents a power of three, starting from the rightmost digit which represents $3^0$. So, we can convert the base three number to base ten by multiplying each digit by its corresponding power of three and then adding up all the values. </think> <answer> We start by writing out the base three number and the corresponding powers of three: \[
\begin{array}{ccccc}
1 & 2 & 0 & 1 & 2 \\
3^4 & 3^3 & 3^2 & 3^1 & 3^0 \\
\end{array}
\] Next, we multiply each digit by its corresponding power of three: \[
\begin{array}{ccccc}
1 & 2 & 0 & 1 & 2 \\
81 & 27 & 0 & 3 & 1 \\
\end{array}
\] Finally, we add up all the values: \[
81 + 27 + 0 + 3 + 1 = 112
\] Therefore, the base ten equivalent of the base three number $12012_3$ is $\boxed{112}$. </answer>

